Instructions:

Requires scikit-learn, numpy, scipy.io, and matplotlib

digits.py is the file for digits classification
You can change variables at the top of the file to change validation and test sizes
File contains 3 functions:

testValidateSVM takes 2 parameters: n and optional parameter cv
n determines training size and cv is the c value (default 1.0)
This function trans and validates an SVM by randomly sampling the given data
This function also draws the confusion matrix. Do not remove the plt.show() at the bottom of the file
Returns accuracy as a decimal

tenFold takes an optional parameter c (c value default 1.0)
performs k-fold validation where k=10
Returns the average accuracy as a decimal

test takes parameter n and optional parameter c
n is the training size and c is the c value (defaul 1.0)
test trains on the given training data then predicts on the kaggle test values
writes to a csv called "results.csv"


spam.py is the file for spam classification
File contains 3 functions:

trainValidate takes parameter n and optional parameter c
n is the training size and c is the c value (defaul 1.0)
Returns accuracy as a decimal

tenFold takes an optional parameter c (c value default 1.0)
performs k-fold validation where k=10
Returns the average accuracy as a decimal

test takes parameter n and optional parameter c
n is the training size and c is the c value (defaul 1.0)
test trains on the given training data then predicts on the kaggle test values
writes to a csv called "spam.csv"
